# SafeMeds API — MongoDB (required for MEAN stack)
#
# This project is configured for MongoDB Atlas (free tier). No Docker or local
# MongoDB install is required.
#
# 1. Create a free account: https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas
# 2. Create a cluster → Database Access: add a user (save username + password)
# 3. Network Access → Add IP Address → "Allow access from anywhere" (0.0.0.0/0) for development
# 4. Connect your application → Drivers → copy the connection string
# 5. Replace <password> with your database user password; set the database path to /safemeds
#
PORT=3000
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://USER:PASSWORD@cluster0.xxxxx.mongodb.net/safemeds?retryWrites=true&w=majority

# Alternative — local MongoDB only if you prefer (e.g. after `npm run mean:db` with Docker):
# MONGODB_URI=mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017/safemeds
#
# Web app (from repo root, SafeMeds/): npm run mean:dev   → API + Angular together
